{{Infobox bus accident |image = [[File:Punjab in Pakistan.svg|250px]] |caption = Location of Punjab in Pakistan |title = 2013 Pakistan gas bus explosion |location = [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]] |country = [[Pakistan]] |date = 25 May 2013 |deaths = 18 |injures = 7 |pax = 23 }}
'''2013 Pakistan gas bus explosion''' occurred on 25 May 2013 after a gas cylinder exploded in a school [[minivan]] heading towards Gujrat in [[Pakistan]]. The blast killed at least 17 people, including 16 children and a bus driver and another 7 children were wounded.<ref name="BBC">{{cite news | url =https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-22664819| title = Pakistan school bus fire kills 16 children|publisher =BBC| accessdate = 25 May 2013| date=2013-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geo.tv/GeoDetail.aspx?ID=102427 |title=16 children, teacher die in Gujrat school bus fire &#124; Pakistan |publisher=geo.tv |date=2013-05-18 |accessdate=2013-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Dawn.Com |url=http://www.beta.dawn.com/news/1013696/gujrat-school-van-cylinder-blast-kills-17-children |title=Gujrat school van cylinder blast kills 17 children |publisher=dawn.com |date=2013-05-25 |accessdate=2013-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2013/05/25/pakistan-bus-fire-children/2360173/ | title=16 children, 1 teacher dead in Pakistan bus fire | publisher=USA Today | accessdate=2013-05-25 | first=Zaheer | last=Babar | date=2013-05-25}}</ref> The children were aged between 6 and 12.<ref name="HP">{{cite news | url =http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/05/25/explosion-pakistan-school-bus_n_3334691.html| title = Gas Cylinder Explosion On Pakistan School Bus Kills 17|publisher =[[The Huffington Post]]| accessdate = 25 May 2013| date=2013-05-25}}</ref><ref name="Guardian">{{cite news | url =https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/may/25/pakistan|title=Pakistan school bus fire kills 16 children|date=2013-05-25|publisher=The Guardian}}</ref>
==Cause== The fire was reportedly caused by a spark when the driver of the dual-fuel bus switched from gas to petrol.<ref name="BBC"/> Officer Ijaz Ahmad said a short-circuit next to a leaking petrol tank started the blaze. Police had earlier blamed an exploding natural gas cylinder.<ref name="Guardian"/>
