{{Infobox dam | name = Kikonge Hydroelectric Power Station | name_official = | image = | image_size = 270px | image_caption = | location_map = Tanzania | location_map_size = 270px | location_map_caption = Location in Tanzania | coordinates = {{coord|10|30|29|S|34|43|46|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Tanzania | location = | purpose = Power, irrigation & flood control | status = P | construction_began = | opening = | demolished = | cost = | owner = [[TANESCO]] | dam_type = | dam_crosses = Ruhuhu River | dam_height = | dam_length = | dam_elevation_crest = | dam_width_crest = | dam_width_base = | dam_volume = {{convert|6000000000|m3|0}} | spillway_count = | spillway_type = | spillway_capacity = | res_name = | res_capacity_total = | res_capacity_active = | res_capacity_inactive= | res_catchment = | res_surface = | res_max_length = | res_max_width = | res_max_depth = | res_elevation = | res_tidal_range = | plant_name = | plant_operator = | plant_commission = 2025 (Expected) | plant_decommission = | plant_type = | plant_hydraulic_head = | plant_turbines = | plant_capacity = {{convert|300|MW|abbr=on}} | plant_capacity_factor= | plant_annual_gen = | website = {{URL|http://www.tanesco.co.tz/}} | footnotes = }}
'''Kikonge Hydroelectric Power Station''' is a proposed {{convert|300|MW|abbr=on}} hydroelectric dam in [[Tanzania]].<ref name="Study">{{cite web|accessdate=31 August 2016|date=12 August 2016| url=http://www.afrotrade.net/detail_news.php?newsid=3177&pageid=2&t=African%20Development%20Bank%20backs%20study%20into%20Tanzania%20hydropower%20and%20dam%20project | title=African Development Bank backs study into Tanzania hydropower and dam project |publisher=Afrotrade.net Quoting Out-law.com |last=Out-law.com}}</ref>
==Location== The power station and the associated dam and water reservoir would be located in the Kikonge area in the [[Ruvuma Region]] in south-western Tanzania.<ref name="Study"/> This is approximately {{convert|130|km|0}}, by road, north-west of [[Songea]], the regional headquarters.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Tanzania_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Songea%2C%20Ruvuma%20Region%2C%20Tanzania&toplace=Ruhuhu%20River%20Ferry%2C%20Mbinga%2C%20Ruvuma%20Region%2C%20Tanzania%2C&dt1=ChIJXynzaVeR_BgRqo30Vy0l4iw&dt2=ChIJsbxmcxOD_RgR9kd-0tyZfD4 | accessdate=31 August 2016 | title=Distance between Songea, Ruvuma Region, Tanzania and Ruhuhu River Ferry, Mbinga, Ruvuma Region, Tanzania | publisher=Globefeed.com | date=31 August 2016 | author=Globefeed.com}}</ref> This is about {{convert|625|km|0}}, by road, south-west of [[Dodoma]], Tanzania's capital.<ref>{{cite web | accessdate=31 August 2016 | date=31 August 2016 | url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Tanzania_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Dodoma%2C%20Dodoma%20Region%2C%20Tanzania&toplace=Ruhuhu%20River%20Ferry%2C%20Mbinga%2C%20Ruvuma%20Region%2C%20Tanzania%2C&dt1=ChIJyX6q7l_lTRgR7pzhYhK_QIA&dt2=ChIJsbxmcxOD_RgR9kd-0tyZfD4 | title=Distance between Dodoma, Dodoma Region, Tanzania and Ruhuhu River Ferry, Mbinga, Ruvuma Region, Tanzania | publisher=Globefeed.com | author=Globefeed.com}}</ref>
==Overview== In August 2016, the [[government of Tanzania]] secured partial funding from the [[African Development Bank]] for a pre-feasibility study for a dam across River Ruhuhu, with a reservoir of {{convert|6000000000|m3|0}}<ref name="Study"/> and capable of generating {{convert|300|MW|abbr=on}} of electricity.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hydroworld.com/articles/2016/08/tanzania-embarking-on-us-2-7-million-pre-feasibility-study-for-proposed-300-mw-kikonge-hydroelectric-facility.html | title=Tanzania embarking on US$2.7 million pre-feasibility study for proposed 300-MW Kikonge hydroelectric facility | accessdate=22 September 2016 | date=5 August 2016 | first=Gregory B. | last=Poindexter | publisher=Hydroworld.com | location=Dar es Salaam}}</ref> As part of the development, a high voltage transmission line, an irrigation scheme, and an agro-business development are also planned.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.theeastafrican.co.ke/business/Tanzania-receives--2m-for-water-and-power-projects-/2560-3360190-qninx4/index.html|title=Tanzania receives $2m for water, power projects | accessdate=31 August 2016 | date=27 August 2016 | first=Apolinari | newspaper=[[The East African]] | location=Nairobi | last=Tairo}}</ref> The pre-feasibility study is expected to last 22 months and the power station, if developed, is expected online in 2025.<ref name="Study"/>
