{{Infobox film | name = Monsoon | image = | alt = | caption = | film name = <!--(for non-English films: film's name in its native language)--> | director = [[Sturla Gunnarsson]] | producer = [[Ina Fichman]] | writer = <!-- or: | writers = --> | screenplay = | story = | based on = <!-- {{based on |[title of the original work] |[writer of the original work]}} --> | starring = | narrator = <!-- or: | narrators = --> | music = [[Andrew T. MacKay]] | cinematography = [[Van Royko]] | editing = [[Nick Hector]] | sound = [[Brice Picard]] | studio = [[Intuitive Pictures]], [[Point du Jour]], and [[Monsoon Ontario]]<ref name="Variety-review">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-monsoon-1201306471/ |title=Film Review: ‘Monsoon’ |author=Dennis Harvey |work=Variety |date=2014-11-04 |accessdate=2015-01-19}}</ref> | distributor = [[KinoSmith]] (Canada) <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kinosmith.com/catalog/246/monsoon/ |title=Monsoon |publisher=KinoSmith Inc. |accessdate=2015-01-19}}</ref> and [[Point du Jour International]] (continental Europe, Japan, and Middle East)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pointdujour-international.com/catalogueFiche.php?idFiche=38198 |title=Monsoon |accessdate=2015-01-19 |publisher=Point du Jour International}}</ref> | released = {{film date |2014|09|07|[[2014 Toronto International Film Festival|Toronto International Film Festival]]}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/sturlagunnarsso/status/505097519073083392 |date=2014-08-28 |title=The Monsoon world premiere will be at TIFF on Sunday September 7. |author=Sturla Gunnarsson (@sturlagunnarsso) |website=Twitter |accessdate=2015-01-19}}</ref> | runtime = 108 minutes | country = Canada and France <ref name="Variety-review"/> | language = English/Hindi/Assamese/Malayalam/Marathi<ref name=TIFF-programme-note>{{cite web |url=http://tiff.net/festivals/ctt14/features/monsoon |title=Monsoon |publisher=TIFF.net |work=Canada's Top Ten Film Festival |accessdate=2015-01-19}}</ref> | budget = | gross = <!--(please use condensed and rounded values, e.g. "£11.6 million" not "£11,586,221")--> }}
'''''Monsoon''''' is a 2014 Canadian documentary film by [[Sturla Gunnarsson]] about the [[monsoon]] weather system [[Climate in India|in India]].
The film was shot in India in the extra-high-definition [[4K resolution|4K format]]<ref name="Variety-review"/> with [[Red Digital Cinema Camera Company#Red Epic|Red Epic]] cameras.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.monsoonmovie.com/about/ |title=Production Notes |accessdate=2015-01-19 |work=Monsoon movie (official site)}}</ref>
The film was included in the list of "Canada's Top Ten" feature films of 2014, selected by a panel of filmmakers and industry professionals organized by TIFF.<ref>{{cite press release |title=TIFF Tips Its Toque to the Best in Canadian Filmmaking: Cronenberg, Dolan, and Gunnarson Among Directors Recognized |date=1 December 2014 |url=http://media.tiff.net.s3.amazonaws.com/content/pdf/14th_Annual_Canadas_Top_Ten_Film_Festival_2014.pdf |publisher=TIFF }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |newspaper=Toronto Star |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2014/12/01/tiffs_top_ten_film_festival_spotlight_on_canadian_film.html |date=1 December 2014 |accessdate=21 December 2014 |author=Linda Barnard |title=TIFF’s Top Ten Film Festival: Spotlight on Canadian film }}</ref> Subsequently the film finished first in the audience balloting, of the features in "Canada's Top Ten".<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://d12gbu3zt5gvms.cloudfront.net/docs/y8JRNP_Award_Winners_Canada%27s_Top_Ten_Film_Festival_8513913_1421100000.pdf |publisher=tiff. |title=Sturla Gunnarsson’s Monsoon crowned Canada's Top Ten Film Festival People’s Choice Award winner |date=2015-01-12 }}</ref><ref name="Star-winner">{{cite web |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2015/01/12/monsoon_canadas_top_ten_peoples_choice_winner.html |newspaper=Toronto Star |title=Monsoon Canada’s Top Ten people’s choice winner |date=2015-01-12 |accessdate=2015-01-19 |author=Linda Barnard }}</ref>
The film will reportedly begin its theatrical run in Toronto on February 27, 2015;<ref name="Star-winner"/> meanwhile Gunnarsson was quoted as being in discussions with an American distributor, following ''Monsoon'''s United States premiere at the 2015 [[Palm Springs International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Hadani Ditmars |date=2015-01-12 |accessdate=2015-01-19 |work=Macleans |url=http://www.macleans.ca/culture/movies/cancon-had-such-a-special-place-in-the-heart-of-palm-springs/ |title=Who knew CanCon had a special place in the heart of Palm Springs? }}</ref>
