'''Parc Cynog''' is a wind farm operated by [[Nuon Renewables]] in Wales.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.nuonrenewables.com/projects/PCNG1 |title= Parc Cynog Wind Farm |website= nuonrenewables.com |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20101207100323/http://www.nuonrenewables.com/projects/PCNG1 |archive-date= 2010-12-07 |access-date= 2017-03-07|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>http://www.manta.com/ic/mvmhccd/gb/parc-cynog-wind-farm-ltd</ref>
Parc Cynog Windfarm was built in 2001. The Windfarm currently consists of 11 turbines.
There were originally five turbines on site which are Micon M1800-750/48 turbines built in 2001, by 2009, a further six turbines were installed by Enercon Wind Energy, the technology used was Enercon E48.
The windfarm is owned by [[Vattenfall]].<ref name=vattenfall>{{cite web|url= https://corporate.vattenfall.co.uk/projects/operational-wind-farms/parc-cynog/ |title= Parc Cynog |website= [[Vattenfall|corporate.vattenfall.co.uk]] |accessdate= 2017-03-07}}</ref>
